                    "body": "{quote}I'm not sure what the question mark is here for but this is a correct statement and would be good to mention. I think Pyarrow is also adding more and more dplyr-like functionality built on top of datasets.\r\n{quote}\r\nI was just unsure of the state of Python + Acero is. My understanding right now is:\r\n # There are some individual functions like {{join}} that use Acero under the hood.\r\n # Once Ibis is a Substrait producer and Acero a consumer, Ibis will be the (dplyr-equivalent) Python API to write queries with deferred execution.\r\n\r\nDoes that sound right?",
